dct_description_sm: Engraved at the Ordnance Survey Office, Southampton. Surveyed in 1879-84 and Published by Colonel Sir C. W. Wilson, K.C.B., F.R.S., R.E., Director General, 1891. Revised in 1897 and Published by Colonel J. Farquharson, C.B., R.E., Director General, 1898 ; Railways inserted to August, 1903
Relief shown by contours and spot heights.
Index maps to adjoining sheets and "to the six inch maps in this sheet."

Shows city plan, various roads and paths, railroads (hand-colored), various locations (windmills, various churches, lighthouses, post and telegraph offices, etc.), woods, marshland, reservoirs, waterways, parks.
